This folder contains the project for the SMN (obnsim-smn).

The source files are in /src; the header files are in /include.
This project uses CMake to build.

Dependencies:
- BOOST graph library (BGL) must be installed and available in the system.
- Google's ProtoBuf must be installed and available in the system.
- At least one supported communication framework must be installed. Currently: YARP. Multiple frameworks may be used in the same binary.

To build the project, simply go to the subdirectory ./build and run the following commands:
  cmake ..
  make

The binary file is put inside ./build.

If this project is included in the root obnsim project as a subproject, refer to the root README file for details. Generally, the binary will be put in the /smn directory of the build directory.